Version 1.0
===========

   Version 1.0 was released 6-Jun-1993:

   @{b}*@{ub} First public release.


@EndNode

@Node "Version 1.07" "phonebill.guide/Version 1.07"
@Next "Version 1.08"
@Prev "Version 1.0"
@Toc "Revision history"

Version 1.07
============

   Version 1.07 was released 14-Jul-1993:

   @{b}*@{ub} Compiled on A4000 :-)

   @{b}*@{ub} All configuration files now use the IFF format, and are stored in
     ENV: and ENVARC:.

   @{b}*@{ub} The documentation is now in guide format.

   @{b}*@{ub} Improved preferences: more options.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added requester that warns you on exit if the configuration has
     been modified.

   @{b}*@{ub} Keyboard shortcuts for most of the gadgets.

   @{b}*@{ub} Requester warning if <from> date is 'above' <to> date.

   @{b}*@{ub} At the beginning of the report you'll now see the time period.

   @{b}*@{ub} If no calls were found during scanning the report will state an
     error message. (In V1.00 an empty textfile would be displayed)

   @{b}*@{ub} Included built-in rates: German, French, Dutch, Swedish rates.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added commandline arguments. Try "Phonebill ?".

   @{b}*@{ub} Added menus to the main window.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added support for MagiCall log file.

   @{b}*@{ub} In the report produced by "List Calls" sometimes only the
     phonenumber would be displayed, although a name was provided in
     the hostmanager.

   @{b}*@{ub} If Phonebill was running under a localized workbench, the default
     from-date ("Yesterday") and to-date ("Today") weren't accepted
     anymore.

   @{b}*@{ub} Fixed some V39 problems: the busy pointer now appears in the same
     resolution as the normal mouse pointer, and some problem
     concerning V39 listviews is fixed too.

   @{b}*@{ub} If you were using a bigger system font the rate exception editor
     would mess up. Also, if you de-zoomed the editor window you
     wouldn't see the exception anymore.


@EndNode

@Node "Version 1.08" "phonebill.guide/Version 1.08"
@Next "Version 1.1"
@Prev "Version 1.07"
@Toc "Revision history"

Version 1.08
============

   Version 1.08 was released 1-Aug-1993:

   @{b}*@{ub} Added Terminus support.

   @{b}*@{ub} Severe bugs were found in Term, Magicall and NComm scanning (thanks
     to Benno Zuure, Henrik Gelius and Frank Petzold). I've rewritten
     all log scanning routines to avoid software failures when unknown
     log messages were encountered.

   @{b}*@{ub} The saved configuration files had the wrong version/revision tag.
     Also, Phonebill would disregard this tag and load any
     configuration file. So if the configuration files need to be
     changed in the future, the old version of the program would load
     the new config files which would probably result in a software
     failure.

   @{b}*@{ub} Under some circumstances phonebill refused to remove a rate,
     although it wasn't in use.


@EndNode

@Node "Version 1.1" "phonebill.guide/Version 1.1"
@Next "Version 2.0"
@Prev "Version 1.08"
@Toc "Revision history"

Version 1.1
===========

   Version 1.1 was released 16-Aug-1993:

   @{b}*@{ub} The host and log lists now show some additional information.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added support for Amiga UUCP timelog.

   @{b}*@{ub} The pre-defined rate "Sverige: Riks 1" was wrong. The exception
     "Monday-Friday 18:00-22:00 0.29 per 52 secs" was missing.


@EndNode

@Node "Version 2.0" "phonebill.guide/Version 2.0"
@Next "Version 2.1"
@Prev "Version 1.1"
@Toc "Revision history"

Version 2.0
===========

   Version 2.0 was released 27-Sep-1993:

   @{b}*@{ub} GUI facelift: windows backfilled, listview doubleclick, changes in
     the menus.

   @{b}*@{ub} Brand new rate editor

   @{b}*@{ub} Improved "Do you really want to quit?" requester.

   @{b}*@{ub} <From> and <To> date are now saved as strings.

   @{b}*@{ub} Iconification.

   @{b}*@{ub} Crippled.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added JrComm support.

   @{b}*@{ub} Binary log file maintenance.

   @{b}*@{ub} Context-sensitive online help, by pressing `help'.

   @{b}*@{ub} New improved documentation, including ASCII and DVI formats.

   @{b}*@{ub} Improved keyboard control: `Escape' will function as a cancel/use
     action, and `return' as an ok/save action.

   @{b}*@{ub} `Skip' in the `Unlisted host found'-requester now really skips the
     host, and not just for once.

   @{b}*@{ub} Now `phonebill' is able to scan a `Terminus 2.0b' log file
     correctly (it has some strange `LF' before its connection string).


@EndNode

@Node "Version 2.1" "phonebill.guide/Version 2.1"
@Next "Version 2.2"
@Prev "Version 2.0"
@Toc "Revision history"

Version 2.1
===========

   Version 2.1 was released 19-Oct-1993:

   @{b}*@{ub} Fixed bug in `trapdoor' scanner: you don't have to pay for
     incoming calls anymore.

   @{b}*@{ub} Fixed bug in `AmigaUUCP' scanner: calls of length greater then 99
     minutes in the UUCP log are misaligned. This caused `phonebill' to
     skip such calls.

   @{b}*@{ub} Now you can add and edit calls from within the binary log file
     editor.

   @{b}*@{ub} Time units extended with upto 4 decimals (e.g. $1,2345 per 12,3456
     seconds).

   @{b}*@{ub} Bugfix: If the textviewer name contained spaces `phonebill'
     couldn't find the viewer.


@EndNode

@Node "Version 2.2" "phonebill.guide/Version 2.2"
@Next "Version 2.3"
@Prev "Version 2.1"
@Toc "Revision history"

Version 2.2
===========

   Version 2.2 was released 7-Dec-1993:

   @{b}*@{ub} Under most circumstances the updating of the binary log file is
     much faster and efficient compared to previous versions.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added MultiFax proffesional support.


@EndNode

@Node "Version 2.3" "phonebill.guide/Version 2.3"
@Next "Version 2.4"
@Prev "Version 2.2"
@Toc "Revision history"

Version 2.3
===========

   Version 2.3 was released 6-Feb-1994:

   @{b}*@{ub} New callrate feature: least costs.

   @{b}*@{ub} The statistics have been improved and new statistics have been
     added (hourly activity).

   @{b}*@{ub} Bugfix: the calls in the binary log file weren't always sorted
     chronologically.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added MicroDot support.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added TrapFax support.

   @{b}*@{ub} Due to the use of the quotes when running the textviewer you
     couldn't specify any commandline arguments (e.g. "WatchIt -i").
     This has been fixed.


@EndNode

@Node "Version 2.4" "phonebill.guide/Version 2.4"
@Next "Version 2.5"
@Prev "Version 2.3"
@Toc "Revision history"

Version 2.4
===========

   Version 2.4 was released 13-Mar-1994:

   @{b}*@{ub} Added TKR-BTX support.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added AutoPilot support.

   @{b}*@{ub} Fixed a problem with the MicroDot log file: A call ending with
     "NETCALL abgebrochen" was not recognized as a valid call, and
     therefore skipped.

   @{b}*@{ub} Any trailing spaces entered at the end of the from/to-date strings
     are ignored now.

   @{b}*@{ub} The `LogScan' signature from the term log file did not have the
     appropriate dateformat. Therefore, it could happen that the
     signature wasn't recognized during some months, which might have
     resulted in `fake' (duplicate) new calls.

   @{b}*@{ub} Generating report now is approx twice as fast due to the use of
     asynchronous I/O.

   @{b}*@{ub} More commandline arguments are supported.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added a "Save"-button in the "Settings not saved" requester.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added `dupe'-detection: duplicate calls are automatically removed.
     So now there is no harm done when a log file is accidently scanned
     twice. I recommend that you re-save your binary log file by
     pressing `Save' in the maintenance panel, so that dupes from
     previous versions are removed (if there were any).


@EndNode

@Node "Version 2.5" "phonebill.guide/Version 2.5"
@Next "Version 3.0"
@Prev "Version 2.4"
@Toc "Revision history"

Version 2.5
===========

   Version 2.5 was released 6-Apr-1994:

   @{b}*@{ub} When adding calls using the maintenance panel the date is
     automatically set to the current date instead of 01-jan-78.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added GPFax support.

   @{b}*@{ub} Bugfix: dupe-detection failed sometimes.

   @{b}*@{ub} AutoPilot problem fixed: only sessions ending with "End of
     Session" were recognized.


@EndNode

@Node "Version 3.0" "phonebill.guide/Version 3.0"
@Next "Version 3.1"
@Prev "Version 2.5"
@Toc "Revision history"

Version 3.0
===========

   Version 3.0 was releaded 25-Aug-1994.

   @{b}*@{ub} The program can now be localized by translating the supplied
     catalog description file.

   @{b}*@{ub} The configuration files have changed from IFF to plain ASCII text
     files which are parsed on startup. Files in ENV:Phonebill are no
     longer needed, which saves memory.

   @{b}*@{ub} Moved from built-in scanners to user-configurable scanners. The
     only built-in scanner left is `GPFax' (which is binary log file).

   @{b}*@{ub} Improved the rates: extended the limit of 4 decimals for units and
     seconds to 9, support for different rates in different time
     periods, you can enter more than one date in a date exception by
     seperating them using a `|' character, first and second unit have
     made place for a listview in which you can configure as much units
     as you wish.

   @{b}*@{ub} Replaced the ugly CON: window by a nice intuition window.

   @{b}*@{ub} You can set a different carrier detect time for each host, or use
     the default carrier detect time as desired.

   @{b}*@{ub} Support for hosts with more than one phone number by seperating
     the numbers using a `|' character.

   @{b}*@{ub} Cleaned up the statistics report a bit. It's also possible to
     define the sort order in which the host listed in the bill report
     are sorted.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added support for `CyberPager', `TheAnswer', `JamMail' and
     `Multifax 2.0'.

   @{b}*@{ub} New user-interface featuring `gtlayout.library' by Olaf `Olsen'
     Barthel. I found this the best compromise between a plain and fast
     gui like the old `phonebill', and a slow but very configurable gui
     like `MUI'.

   @{b}*@{ub} Re-arranged the menus. I noticed that the `Project' menu was called
     `Projects', which looks very ugly. Why didn't anyone report this?
     :)

   @{b}*@{ub} Cleaned up the code: large parts have been re-written.

   @{b}*@{ub} Installation is now done by using the Commodore Installer (or
     should that be Samsung Installer, or Philips Installer? :-)


@EndNode

@Node "Version 3.1" "phonebill.guide/Version 3.1"
@Next "Version 3.1a"
@Prev "Version 3.0"
@Toc "Revision history"

Version 3.1
===========

   Version 3.1 was releaded 4-Oct-1994.

   @{b}*@{ub} Changed: the program now also looks for the keyfile in the
     directory specified by the KEYPATH variable, if it exists.

   @{b}*@{ub} Changed: The cookie %a only accepted certain phonenumbers, which
     caused a lot of problems. Now %a accepts any string.  So now,
     "Calling %n (%a)" and "Calling BBS (123-AMI)" match.  "A BBS 123"
     and "%n %a" match too: name="A" nr="BBS 123", to resolve this "%n
     %A" should be used.

   @{b}*@{ub} Bug fix: Updating the binary log files on MC68000-amigas could
     crash because of reading from an odd address.

   @{b}*@{ub} Changed: when adding hosts the last selected rate will be used as
     default for a new unlisted host.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added an option called `connection costs' to the rates.

   @{b}*@{ub} Changed: if  "ENV:AmigaGuide/Path" is set up correctly, you can
     put the guide file "Phonebill.guide" where ever you want.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added some average costs/calls/online per day to the stats.  Also,
     if the <to date> is set somewhere in the future, `phonebill' will
     estimate the total costs on that date (bill report).

   @{b}*@{ub} Changed: hosts with multiple phonenumbers did not work the way it
     was supposed to be. For example, now you can group a host "Line A"
     (9111) and host "Line B" (9112) to "Lines" (9111|9112).

   @{b}*@{ub} New: Hosts can be assigned to groups, over which reports can be
     generated seperately, for example: create a group called "Poll"
     and assign all hosts you poll for mail to this group.  Then you
     can view reports concerning these hosts only...

   @{b}*@{ub} Bug fix: the `minimal costs' weren't saved.

   @{b}*@{ub} By pressing `Cancel' in the host settings panel the changes to the
     host were dropped, but changes to the rates weren't.  Now, you can
     only pick a rate from within the host settings panel. Editting
     rates is done by using the rate editor.

   @{b}*@{ub} The format of the configuration files has changed again.  For
     example: "scanner ... endscanner" is now "(scanner ...)" The new
     format is more compact, and the parser should be a bit faster
     compared to the old parser.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added German and Swedish catalogs, updated Swedish rates.

   @{b}*@{ub} And last but not least: my fido e-mail addresses have changed. :)


@EndNode

@Node "Version 3.1a" "phonebill.guide/Version 3.1a"
@Next "Version 3.2"
@Prev "Version 3.1"
@Toc "Revision history"

Version 3.1a
============

   Version 3.1a was released 14-Oct-1994.
   @{b}*@{ub} The unregistered version could crash when you were presented with
     the shareware requester, but only if the localized strings were
     larger than the original strings.

   @{b}*@{ub} Fixed possible software failures in the routines responsible for
     adding hosts manually.

   @{b}*@{ub} Removed a spelling mistake. :-)

   @{b}*@{ub} An italian catalog has been added.


@EndNode

@Node "Version 3.2" "phonebill.guide/Version 3.2"
@Next "Version 3.3"
@Prev "Version 3.1a"
@Toc "Revision history"

Version 3.2
===========

   Version 3.2 was released 24-Dec-1994.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added NewIcons and MagicWB icons to the distribution.

   @{b}*@{ub} The program no longer requires both %I and %X or %U and %I to be
     present to determine the length of the call. An occurence of %X
     only suffices.

   @{b}*@{ub} Re-added writing signatures to the GPFax log file. If you don't
     like this, turn it off in the log settings.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added scanners for AmiTel, Off-line Amiga, DreamTerm,
     ISDN-Master-Telephone-Log.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added a new cookie for fido-style addresses to the scanner.  If
     you have `traplist' installed the address found will be used to
     find the real name and phonenumber of the host.  You'll need to
     configure the "Nodelist path" (see miscellaneous settings).

   @{b}*@{ub} Phonebill has become a commodity: a hotkey can be defined in the
     tooltypes (CX_POPKEY, defaults to "ctrl alt b") to (de)iconify the
     program.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added: if you want to rescan the log files you won't have to go
     through the trouble of removing the signatures with a text editor,
     just use the new `Rescan logs' menu item.

   @{b}*@{ub} New: option for disabling writing signatures to the log file

   @{b}*@{ub} Changed: a signature will only be added if new calls were found.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added new date format: an integer can be used to specify the
     number of days after today (e.g. scanning from "-6" up to "today"
     results in a report of the last seven days.

   @{b}*@{ub} New: report presets (for the scan range and groups).

   @{b}*@{ub} New hosts can be automatically added by supplying the rate(s) with
     a pattern to match certain area codes.

   @{b}*@{ub} Fixed a problem in call appending.


@EndNode

@Node "Version 3.3" "phonebill.guide/Version 3.3"
@Next "Version 3.3a"
@Prev "Version 3.2"
@Toc "Revision history"

Version 3.3
===========

   @{b}*@{ub} Added a new `cookie' for scanning a localized date (e.g. newer
     versions of autopilot started logging localized dates).  Help, I
     am running out of cookies! :-)

   @{b}*@{ub} Accidently mapped the month string "maa" (dutch for March) to may.
     Also, "mär" was unknown.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added support for Plink.

   @{b}*@{ub} A linefeed at the end of the bill report was missing.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added AutoPilot scanner for v1.75 or higher.

   @{b}*@{ub} The program can be opened on a public screen.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added option to process log files on startup.

   @{b}*@{ub} Bug fix: somewhere in the log panel information from memory was
     read after it had been freed already, causing enforcer hits. Oops!

   @{b}*@{ub} Added commandline switch "CONFIG/S" to specify the location of the
     configuration directory.

   @{b}*@{ub} Fixed bugs in the terminus scanner.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added a scanner for ZeeTerm.

   @{b}*@{ub} When pressing `enter' in the from/to gadgets of the rate period
     settings panel the date(s) or day(s) settings panel could popup
     with no particular reason. This has been fixed.

   @{b}*@{ub} Cosmetical changes: menu checkmarks and Amiga keys are now scaled
     according to the current screen display ratio, added a zoom gadget
     to all windows.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added a new truncating option called "Preserve blocks". If this
     option is enabled the log file will be truncated at the position
     of an empty line seperator.

   @{b}*@{ub} Monetary values are now displayed according to the current locale
     settings.

   @{b}*@{ub} Removed my name and address from .cd file.


@EndNode

@Node "Version 3.3a" "phonebill.guide/Version 3.3a"
@Next "Version 3.3b"
@Prev "Version 3.3"
@Toc "Revision history"

Version 3.3a
============

   Version 3.3a was released 11-Apr-1995.

   @{b}*@{ub} The executable from the previous release was mangled: AmigaDOS
     2.04 wasn't able to execute it, but for some reason AmigaDOS 3.0+
     didn't have any problems with it. Needless to say that it has been
     fixed...


@EndNode

@Node "Version 3.3b" "phonebill.guide/Version 3.3b"
@Next "Version 3.3c"
@Prev "Version 3.3a"
@Toc "Revision history"

Version 3.3b
============

   Version 3.3b was released 17-Jun-1995.

   @{b}*@{ub} A French translation is now available, thanks to Cedric Souchon.

   @{b}*@{ub} Important note: Continental Drift (the Australian  registration
     site) is closing down, meaning that they no longer accept
     registrations. Ofcourse, it is always possible for Australian
     people to get registered by me directly.

   @{b}*@{ub} A switch is now available to make sure that the reports contain
     ASCII characters only (Miscellaneous settings).

   @{b}*@{ub} "Off-line Amiga" scanner modified to recognize sessions other than
     "girotel" (e.g. Rabobank).

   @{b}*@{ub} Added GMS scanner.


@EndNode

@Node "Version 3.3c" "phonebill.guide/Version 3.3c"
@Next "Version 3.3d"
@Prev "Version 3.3b"
@Toc "Revision history"

Version 3.3c
============

   Version 3.3c was released 10-Aug-1995.

   @{b}*@{ub} Scanner.config: Added PPP scanner.

   @{b}*@{ub} Scanner.config: term's action log scanner now reads localized
     dates as written by term. However, this is only of any use when you
     are using a non-localized term on a localized workbench since
     otherwise phonebill wouldn't understand term's localized log file
     anyway. Btw, the best thing would be to use the call log anyway.

   @{b}*@{ub} Finally the install script has been localized as well.

   @{b}*@{ub} Bug fix: The last line of a log file was ignored if and only if it
     didn't contain a line feed. As far as I know, the only log file
     format that doesn't end it's lines with an apropriate linefeed is
     TKR-BTX.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added UK rates.

   @{b}*@{ub} Bug fix, 2.04 only: if you didn't specify a date in the rate
     period settings panel it would be interpreted as "31-Dec-99".
     This wasn't really my fault :), kick 2.04 seems to accept "-" as a
     valid date (try running "date -" in a shell).

   @{b}*@{ub} Scanner.config: modified trapdoor scanner to recognize calls were
     the modem could not be hung up.

   @{b}*@{ub} Scanner.config: modified the trapdoor scanner to recognize calls
     that were breaked by the user ("[..]User break[..]").

   @{b}*@{ub} Scanner.config: GMS scanner has been modified to process 5D
     addresses correctly.


@EndNode

@Node "Version 3.3d" "phonebill.guide/Version 3.3d"
@Next "Version 3.4"
@Prev "Version 3.3c"
@Toc "Revision history"

Version 3.3d
============

   Version 3.3d was released 11-Nov-1995.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added support for Prometheus.

   @{b}*@{ub} The PPP scanner has been removed as it doesn't seem to work
     without tweaking with the logfile. To compensate, I've added an
     ARexx script that produces call log compatible output.  With some
     slight modifications it can be made to work with AmiTCP, e.g. by
     putting it in the startnet/stopnet scripts. The script can be
     found in the `Extras' directory.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added support for Online-o-Meter. See @{"Supported log files" Link "Supported log files"}.

   @{b}*@{ub} The Belgium rates have been updated. Read the accompanying `ReadMe'
     in the `Documentation' directory. Thanks to Philippe Duchenne.

   @{b}*@{ub} The Swedish rates have been updated for 1996, thanks to Thomas
     Andersson.

   @{b}*@{ub} Fixed a program failure that occured when scanning an empty log
     file.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added ZerMailer scanner.


@EndNode

@Node "Version 3.4" "phonebill.guide/Version 3.4"
@Next "Version 3.4a"
@Prev "Version 3.3d"
@Toc "Revision history"

Version 3.4
===========

   Version 3.4 was released 23-Mar-1996.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added support for OnlineMeter (not to be mistaken with
     Online-O-Meter).

   @{b}*@{ub} I received several updated german rates. Ofcourse, only one of them
     could be included in this release.

   @{b}*@{ub} Swedish rates have been updated.

   @{b}*@{ub} The ISDN scanners (ISDN Master, ISDN Wilhelmtel) have been updated.

   @{b}*@{ub} Fixed a rare bug which caused costs to be estimated even though
     the `To date' was not set to a future date.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added new scanner for Zodiac's point 37.211+.

   @{b}*@{ub} Jacob Laursen send in a Danish translation and the Danish rates.

   @{b}*@{ub} For no reason at all the length of a signatures was limited to 80
     characters. Fixed.

   @{b}*@{ub} Created a seperate panel for the area codes, where they can be
     comfortably edited and ordered.

   @{b}*@{ub} Phonebill now also looks for a file named
     "Config/User-Scanner.config" when reading log scanners. Scanners
     created for your own use for your own use should be put here.  If
     you stick to this rule, you won't have to worry about loosing any
     scanners when upgrading to a new "Scanner.config" file.

   @{b}*@{ub} The Install script has been localized (German) by Steffen
     Salzmann. He also revised the German catalog for the program.
     Thanks.

   @{b}*@{ub} Changes in the `From'/`To' string gadgets of the main panel were
     not recognized in the case that the gadget was deactivated by
     moving the mouse away from it and clicking elsewhere. Fixed!

   @{b}*@{ub} Increased the maximum string length of the `Area codes pattern' in
     the rate settings panel.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added support for uucico (UUCP).

   @{b}*@{ub} Added support for MailKick.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added support for MagicCX.

   @{b}*@{ub} Unfortunately, I lost the e-mail addresses of the persons who
     created the Norwegian and French translations. The catalogs are now
     outdated, and are removed from the distribution.


@EndNode

@Node "Version 3.4a" "phonebill.guide/Version 3.4a"
@Next "Version 3.5"
@Prev "Version 3.4"
@Toc "Revision history"

Version 3.4a
============

   Version 3.4a was released 1-Nov-1996.

   @{b}*@{ub} The "LANGUAGE" tooltype is now honoured.

   @{b}*@{ub} Philippe Duchenne updated the French translation. He also updated
     the Belgium rates. See Contrib/ for additional AreaCodes
     configuration files

   @{b}*@{ub} Falk Krause updated the German rates.

   @{b}*@{ub} The distribution now also includes Autrian rates, thanks to
     Richter Arno.

   @{b}*@{ub} New Italian rates were sent in by Mattia Cococcioni.

   @{b}*@{ub} Fixed Term call-log scanner to ignore "???" as a valid host name.

   @{b}*@{ub} Fixed possible crashes when pressing `Save' in several panels.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added scanner for Miami.

   @{b}*@{ub} Updated the Danish rates, thanks to Jacob Laursen. He also added
     an area codes configuration setup for Denmark. See the Contrib/
     directory.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added support for ZMailer, sent in by Jacob Laursen.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added support for Gotcha!, sent in by Falk Krause.

   @{b}*@{ub} Matthias Kraft updated Zodiac's Point scanner.

   @{b}*@{ub} The install script is now translated to Dansk.


@EndNode

@Node "Version 3.5" "phonebill.guide/Version 3.5"
@Next "Version 3.5a"
@Prev "Version 3.4a"
@Toc "Revision history"

Version 3.5
===========

   Version 3.5 was released 7-Mar-1997.

   @{b}*@{ub} Besides the built-in log file truncation, you can now also run a
     (shell) command when a log file exceeds its size. For example,
     settings the command to `delete "%f"' deletes the log file.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added a new rate feature: billing per second.

   @{b}*@{ub} Thomas Andersson updated the Swedish rates.

   @{b}*@{ub} When selecting groups in the "Groups" pull-down menu, the entry
     "Default" is now automatically unchecked when you choose any group.

   @{b}*@{ub} I updated the Dutch rates to include tax (NLG 0.165 instead of
     (NLG 0.15). Warning: cost calculation is only two-decimals
     accurate for unregistered users!.

   @{b}*@{ub} New Italian rates, sent in by Francesco Dipietromaria.

   @{b}*@{ub} Jacob Laursen updated the Danish rates. See Contrib/Danmark.

   @{b}*@{ub} Changes to the host name/phone number in the host settings panel
     were only recognized if you pressed enter in the string gadgets.
     Fixed.

   @{b}*@{ub} The program didn't pay proper attention to the stack size, which
     resulted in random crashes.

   @{b}*@{ub} Rate panel: copying dates/days resulted in possible weird crashes
     during further usage.

   @{b}*@{ub} Thanks to Philippe Duchenne for updating the Belgium rates. See
     Contrib/Belgium.

   @{b}*@{ub} RED ALERT: my e-mail address has changed.  Although the old one
     will remain valid for some time, please use raymondp@win.tue.nl in
     the future.

   @{b}*@{ub} Modified the Xenolink scanner to accept times that specify the
     seconds as well.

   @{b}*@{ub} The Miami scanner has changed. Due to a misunderstanding of the
     log format, the scanner wasn't correct. Thanks to Philippe
     Duchenne and Andreas Hille for pointing this out.

   @{b}*@{ub} Tinkered with the host matching algorithm. For example:
        @{b}*@{ub} The hosts list contains one entry "A (123)".

        @{b}*@{ub} A log is scanned, containing a call to "A (456)"

        @{b}*@{ub} Phone numbers 123 and 456 belong to the same host, but are
          from *different* phone companies (meaning different rates).

        @{b}*@{ub} Previously, the new call "A (456)" would be matched to the
          host entry "A (123)", so both calls area would be accounted
          with the same rate. This is no longer the case.  Now, the
          match would only have been made if host "A" really has listed
          "456" as an alternative phone number (e.g. "A (123|456)").

        @{b}*@{ub} As said, the match is not made. So, "A (456)" is treated as
          if it were a new host. So, the areacodes patterns are
          consulted to see if "456" can be automatically matched to a
          rate. If this is possible, we distinguish two cases:
             @{b}*@{ub} The matched rate equals the rate of the host named "A"
               that was already known. In this case, number "456" would
               be added as a second phone number to host "A".

             @{b}*@{ub} the matched rate does not equal the rate of the host
               named "A". In this case, a *new* host named "A" will be
               created. So now two hosts named "A" exist!

   @{b}*@{ub} It's now possible to enter a negative carrier detect time value.

   @{b}*@{ub} No support for the PhoneLog standard (1) yet. PhoneLog will be
     supported as soon as a shared library becomes available.

   ---------- Footnotes ----------

   (1)  http://www.informatik.uni-bremen.de/~i07m/PhoneLog.html


@EndNode

@Node "Version 3.5a" "phonebill.guide/Version 3.5a"
@Next "Version 3.6"
@Prev "Version 3.5"
@Toc "Revision history"

Version 3.5a
============

   Version 3.5a was released 10-May-1997.

   @{b}*@{ub} A Serbian translation is available. Thanks to Ivan Sofic for
     translating and Marko Antonovic for proofreading.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added support for TimeConnect.

   @{b}*@{ub} Fixed (possible) enforcer hits during host-call matching (e.g.
     while generating a report).

   @{b}*@{ub} Under some rare circumstances, 100 cents could be displayed as
     "$0,100" instead of $1,00". Fixed.

   @{b}*@{ub} The hosts weren't sorted properly in the bill report. Fixed.

   @{b}*@{ub} Mattia Cococcioni updated Italian rates.


@EndNode

@Node "Version 3.6" "phonebill.guide/Version 3.6"
@Prev "Version 3.5a"
@Toc "Revision history"

Version 3.6
===========

   Version 3.6 was released 28-Dec-1997.

   @{b}*@{ub} In the maintenace panel a "Copy" button is added, allowing the
     user to easily duplicate entries.

   @{b}*@{ub} Re-arranged the log settings panel, by making use of tabs.

   @{b}*@{ub} You can no longer accept a rate period when it contains invalid
     dates. Furthermore, Modifications to the dates were not recognized
     as changes to your configuration. Fixed.

   @{b}*@{ub} You can no longer accept a preset (by clicking "Use") when it
     contains invalid dates.

   @{b}*@{ub} New presets now have some defaults setup.

   @{b}*@{ub} Too many presets could cause the program to crash. Fixed.

   @{b}*@{ub} Philippe Duchenne updated the Belgium rates (See
     "Contrib/Belgium/Belgium-rates.README").

   @{b}*@{ub} The data listed in the statistics report no longer take future
     days into account. If there are a lot of days ahead, phonebill
     used to assume that no calls would take place during that period,
     which was not realistic at all.

   @{b}*@{ub} The preset/rate period date ranges were not validated. Fixed.

   @{b}*@{ub} If you have many groups, the group check boxes in the host
     settings panel and preset panel are now divided into two columns,
     to prevent that the window would get too tall.

   @{b}*@{ub} The <From>/<To> string gadgets in the rate period settings panel
     are now checked for valid dates. A message appears in case of an
     invalid date.

   @{b}*@{ub} The input of the presets panel was not blocked when adding a new
     preset. Fixed.

   @{b}*@{ub} You can now choose to automatically generate a report on start-up.

   @{b}*@{ub} Re-arranged the miscellaneous settings panel, by making use of
     tabs.

   @{b}*@{ub} A preset could accidentally be displayed in the groups pull-down
     menu. Fixed.

   @{b}*@{ub} Calls having a phone number no longer matched hosts that didn't
     have phone numbers. Fixed.

   @{b}*@{ub} Added a "Remove all" button to the hosts panel.

   @{b}*@{ub} When selecting "Default" in the "Groups" pull-down menu, all other
     selected groups are autommatically unchecked.

   @{b}*@{ub} When an error occurred while parsing the configuration files, a
     mutilated error message (or none at all) would appear. Fixed.

   @{b}*@{ub} If the truncate percentage (log settings panel) was modified, a
     bad log configuration file would be written. Fixed.

   @{b}*@{ub} Phonebill is now compiled using gcc.

   @{b}*@{ub} Henrik Brautaset Aronsen sent in new Norwegian rates.

   @{b}*@{ub} Modified the Miami scanner to cope with the 3.x log file format.

   @{b}*@{ub} Fredrik Ismyren sent in a scanner for AmiSMS.

   @{b}*@{ub} Fredrik Ismyren updated the Swedish rates (See
     "contrib/Sverige/Sverige-rates.README").

   @{b}*@{ub} Added support for NetTime log files. Please read the section
     "Supported log files" for more information.


@EndNode

